@startuml
title FOD 3.2.20 — komponenty i przepływ danych file read

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Użytkownik / msfind" as User

package "fod-indexer" {
  component "CLI\ncli.rs" as CLI
  component "Dyspozytor\nmain.rs" as Main
  component "File Read API\nfile_read_api.rs" as ReadAPI
  component "Hashing\nhash.rs" as Hash
  component "JSON serializer\nserde + Base64" as Json
  component "Raw output\nstdout / stderr" as Raw
}

database "PostgreSQL" as PG {
  component "index_files" as IndexFiles
  component "index_sources" as IndexSources
  component "index_file_hashes" as IndexHashes
}

folder "Zarejestrowane źródło plików" as Source {
  file "source_root/path" as File
}

User --> CLI : file read --id\n[offset, length]
CLI --> Main : FileCommands::Read
Main --> ReadAPI : read_file()

ReadAPI --> IndexFiles : SELECT stabilnego file_id
ReadAPI --> IndexSources : SELECT nazwy, rodzaju,\nroot_path
ReadAPI --> IndexHashes : SELECT partial/full hash\ni observed metadata

ReadAPI --> File : canonicalize, open RO,\nmetadata, seek, read
ReadAPI --> Hash : partial SHA-256\nfull SHA-256
Hash --> File : odczyt z tego samego uchwytu

ReadAPI --> Json : provenance + validation\n+ range + bytes
ReadAPI --> Raw : provenance + bytes

Json --> User : stdout: JSON\nbytes jako Base64
Raw --> User : stderr: provenance\nstdout: surowe bajty

note right of PG
Tylko SELECT.
Brak modyfikacji:
- index_files
- index_sources
- index_file_hashes
end note

note right of Source
Tylko odczyt.
Brak zapisu, zmiany nazw,
usuwania lub markerów.
end note

note bottom of ReadAPI
Granica bezpieczeństwa:
1. walidacja rekordu indeksu,
2. bezpieczna ścieżka,
3. snapshot przed,
4. hash,
5. odczyt zakresu,
6. snapshot po,
7. dopiero wtedy emisja danych.
end note
@enduml
